AGI -&nbsp;The traffic light pole under which the 19-year-old of Egyptian nationalities Ramy Elgaml died, at the end of a pursuit of the carabinieri took place on the night of 24 November 2024, was dismantled and disposed of by the Amsa, the company of the waste of Milan, as evidenced by the photographs to the acts of the prosecutor's investigation.&nbsp; That's what you learn in investigative environments. Of the existence of this pole had repeatedly asked the magistrates the approach Barbara Indovina, who assists the family of the young passenger of the scooter driven by Fares Bouzidi and long pursued by the carabinieri for not stopping. According to the lawyer, the pole, "fundamental element" to be analyzed to reconstruct the dynamics of the incident, should have been seized in the imminence of the facts. And instead, as he wrote in an e-mail of 8 February last the engineer Marco Romaniello, commissioned by the prosecutor of a cinematic investigation whose conclusions will be delivered to those investigating in a couple of days, this pole "was resigned from A2A two days after the accident".
